
Reflection API
- using reflection api we can analyze our java classes.
- Reflection API is used to analyze the Software.
- To load a class in another class we have to use Class.forName()
    syntax:
      Class clz=Class.forName("fullycolifiedclassname");
      Field[] fields =clz.getDeclaredFields();


      Q What is API ..?
      set of predefine classes. to perform a one operations.

    - Reflection API classes are placed in three packages.
        1) java.lang;
        2) java.lang.reflect
        3) java.lang.annotation

